topic.title: Pin Descriptions

body.p: The following section describes the pins of the HB20 device.

table.title: QFN and CSP Pin and Ball Functions

entry.p: HB_WS QFN-48 Pin No. (for reference only)
Manufacturing test supply. Connect to board VSS.
Analog GND. Connect to board VSS.
RF VSS. Connect to board VSS.
PA supply, to be connected to either VSUP or VDDD.
Internal reference output voltage. Connect to VSS if audio applications are not required and to external capacitor if audio applications are required.
Analog IO 0 used for monitoring external signals. Leave to float if not used.
Analog IO 1 used for monitoring external signals. Leave to float if not used.
Analog IO 2 used for monitoring external signals. Leave to float if not used.
Analog IO 3 used for monitoring external signals. Leave to float if not used.
Wake-up enable input. Keep low when not required. Please note that this input is used in conjunction with RESET_B to invoke service mode.
System reset input (full chip reset low). Internal 500 kΩ pull-up included on this pin.
General programmable digital input only (default) or XO32KI (32 kHz crystal oscillator amplifier input).
General programmable digital input only (default) or XO32KO (32 kHz crystal oscillator amplifier output).
Buck mode select input. Connect to VSS if buck is not required.
Optional external 32.768 kHz input clock. Connect to VSS if not used.
Analog core voltage regulator output. Connect to external load capacitor.
Buck output voltage pin. Connect to external capacitor or VBATT depending on whether buck mode or non-buck mode is required.
Digital core voltage regulator output. Connect to external load capacitor.
Buck or boost VSS. Connect to board VSS.
Buck switching output. Connect to external inductor when buck is used, otherwise leave not connected.
Digital VSS. Connect to board VSS.
32 MHz crystal oscillator output. Connect to external crystal.
32 MHz crystal oscillator input. Connect to external crystal.
Boost converter output. Connect to load capacitor.
